How would you write a C word program module for the conversion of decimal number values to Binary numbers?
Illustration: 0 to 00000, 1 to 00001, 2 to 00010, 9 to 00101, 10 to 00110, 15 to 00111 and so on. Please help in coding. The solution would likely involve using bitwise operators and shifts in C to iteratively divide the decimal number by 2 and keep track of the remainders, which will form the binary number when reversed.
```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>

void decimalToBinary(int n) {
    int binaryNum[32];
    int i = 0;
    while (n > 0) {
        binaryNum[i] = n % 2;
        n = n / 2;
        i++;
    }
    for (int j = i - 1; j >= 0; j--)
        printf("%d", binaryNum[j]);
}

int main() {
    int decimal;
    printf("Enter a decimal number: ");
    scanf("%d", &decimal);
    printf("Binary equivalent: ");
    decimalToBinary(decimal);
    printf("\n");
    return 0;
}
```

